## 2026-03-28 - "Did you mean this token?" nudge
- Implemented a "Did you mean this token?" nudge that suggests existing tokens when a raw value is entered that closely matches an existing token's resolved value. Works in two surfaces: the TokenEditor drawer (replaces the old exact-match-only alias suggestion) and inline editing in the token tree (shows a nudge row after saving a raw value).
- Created `useNearbyTokenMatch` hook that finds tokens within perceptual distance thresholds: ΔE < 5 for colors (using CIELAB), ≤2px or ≤10% for dimensions (same unit), ≤5% for numbers. Debounced at 150ms. Returns top 3 matches sorted by distance with "Exact" (<1 ΔE / 0 diff) or "Close" labels.
- Created `TokenNudge` component with single-match and multi-match layouts: accent-colored dashed border, color swatches for color tokens, ΔE distance display, accept/dismiss buttons.

